abstract: Voters in Netherlands overwhelmingly reject nonbinding referendum on trade and cooperation agreement between European Union and Ukraine, with 61.1 percent of voters in opposition to deal; vote raises questions about future of accord and indicates how fragile support for European is even as it deals with multiple crises.
lead_paragraph: In a nonbinding election, voters in the Netherlands said no to a trade and cooperation pact. All 28 member countries must approve the deal.

headline.main: Dutch Referendum Rejects Trade Deal Between E.U. and Ukraine
headline.print_headline: Dutch Voters Reject Deal Between E.U. and Ukraine
